cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.PF, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the impact of wireless traffic on the performance of wireless networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper uses tools from queueing theory to model the traffic. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as the paper considers the spatial distribution of users and traffic. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper evaluates the performance of wireless networks under different traffic statistics. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is less likely but still possible as the paper considers the behavior of multiple users in a wireless network.
